groups/rbac.md
# Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

RBAC allows administrators to grant only the permissions required for a user's job.

Examples

Global Administrator

- Full tenant administration

User Administrator

- Create users
- Reset passwords
- Manage group memberships

Help Desk Administrator

- Password resets
- Unlock accounts

Benefits

- Least Privilege
- Reduced security risk
- Easier auditing
conditional-access/overview.md
# Conditional Access

Conditional Access evaluates sign-in requests before allowing access to Microsoft resources.

Common Conditions

- User
- Device Compliance
- Location
- Risk Level
- Application

Example Policy

IF

User = Employees

AND

Device = Compliant

THEN

Allow Access

ELSE

Require MFA
authentication/mfa.md# Multi-Factor Authentication

MFA strengthens account security by requiring multiple forms of authentication.

Common Methods

- Microsoft Authenticator
- SMS
- Phone Call
- FIDO2 Security Keys
- Windows Hello for Business

Benefits

- Protects against password theft
- Reduces account compromise
- Supports Zero Trust security
authentication/sspr.md
# Self-Service Password Reset (SSPR)

SSPR allows users to securely reset forgotten passwords without contacting the help desk.

Verification Methods

- Authenticator App
- Phone Number
- Email
- Security Questions

Advantages

- Faster recovery
- Reduced help desk workload
- Improved user experience
docs/security-best-practices.md
# Identity Security Best Practices

- Enable MFA for all users
- Use Conditional Access
- Follow Least Privilege
- Regularly review administrator roles
- Monitor sign-in logs
- Remove inactive accounts
- Enable passwordless authentication when possible
- Audit guest users regularly
